  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (various countries)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Regulatory Mechanisms:\n- Customer due diligence procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing between financial institutions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement robust anti-money laundering programs\n- Regular training for employees\n- Maintaining detailed transaction records\n- Implementing risk assessment protocols\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
